    <title>Exciter</title>
    <p>
        An exciter is used to enhance a signal by dynamic equalization, phase
        manipulation, harmonic synthesis of high frequency signals, and through the
        addition of subtle harmonic distortion.
    </p>
    <p>
        PulseEffects uses the exciter plugin developed by
        <link href="https://calf-studio-gear.org" its:translate="no">Calf Studio</link>.
    </p>
    <terms>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Amount</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                The amount of harmonics added to the original signal
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Harmonics</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                The amount of newly created harmonics
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Scope</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                The frequency harmonics are produced above
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Ceiling(button)</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Constrain the excitement on the upper end
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Ceiling(value)</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                The frequency no harmonics are produced above
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Blend Harmonics</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                The "colour" (or octave) of the harmonics
            </p>
        </item>
        <item>
            <title>
                <em style="strong">Listen</em>
            </title>
            <p>
                Mute the original signal and listen to the harmonics exclusively
            </p>
        </item>
    </terms>
